fields.value: Harris 1976 New York State Teachers Survey, study no. 2520

dsDescriptionValue.value:
Survey of New York State United Teachers Union members investigates attitudes toward higher education in the state and the job the organization is doing.

Questions include rating of NYSUT in representing its members' interests, political influence, social and labor issues, satisfaction with leadership, publications, and membership benefits.

fields.value: Subject: Study Level Error Note, Notes: Harris surveyed various groups for the NY State United Teachers: United University Professors members (SUNY) and Professional Staff Congress members (CUNY); New York City Chapter Chairperson; Teachers; Upstate local presidents; and Upstate membership and NYC membership. Attitudes on various topics were collected by questionnaire in a face- to-face interview;Type: ODUM:ACCESS.CATEGORY Notes: I;Type: ODUM:CODEBOOK.NUMBER Notes: H-2520;
